HTTP post and get have system info in the header
To get them

for (var name in req.headers) req.headers[name] < something


Responses also have headers, including content type. This superceeds file types. Also contain server metadata
* Requests can have bodies as well
* Post type commonly application/x-www-form-urlencoded, or multipart/form-data

Request API on page 60

Response: The thing you use to dictate what the client gets.
API on page 61

Common functions:
* Rendering content
	* 65: Take template, pass params, send that off
* Dealing with forms

EG: app.post('/process-contact', function(req, res) {
	do things

});

Parameter syntax
* app.put('api/tour/:id', function...) < adds an id field to req.params